    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nto me the current behavior of calling `:split` in a floatwin is more like an undefined behavior, and in my use it always causes troubles and making writing plugins use floatwin more diffcult. so why not just disable `:sp`/`:vs` for floatwins?\r\n\r\ni recently had the need to use few fullscreen floatwins, and then i found myself always doing `:sp`/`:vs` and it causes troubles as `:sp` creates new window so that the `winleave` event is triggered, when i realized i'm doing wrong, `:q` will trigger `winclosed` and other events. from my past experience, working with floatwins autocmds are heavily used and necessary, and dealing with such a misuse of `:sp` is unnecessary complicated.\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\n`:sp`/`:vs` have no effect to floatwins",
